 treatment; and saving through insurance. This detailed summary of the saving incentives of the G-7 nations will be an invaluable reference for policymakers and academics interested in personal saving behavior.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSaving and investment -- Government policy. 0aSaving and investmentxGovernment policy. 0aTaxation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  ainsurance, saving, tax shelters, social security, pension, retirement, capital income, taxation, debt, household savings, united kingdom, japan, italy, germany, france, canada, g-7 nations, finance, economics, nonfiction, thrift, investment, policy, government, inflation, poverty, wealth, aging, inequity, welfare, intervention, regulation, 401k, ira.1 aBanks, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlundell, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurbidge, John B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBörsch-Supan, Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, James B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFougère, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIto, Takatoshi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJappelli, Tullio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitamura, Yukinobu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPagano, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoterba, James M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoterba, James M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eB